{"id":1484,"date":"2011-06-02T06:37:53","date_gmt":"2011-06-02T11:37:53","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/m_opposite_w.php"},"modified":"2011-06-02T06:37:53","modified_gmt":"2011-06-02T11:37:53","slug":"m_opposite_w","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/m_opposite_w.php","title":{"rendered":"M Opposite W"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mccann_wg_logo.gif\" alt=\"McCann Worldgroup Logo, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Established in 1997 <a href=\"http:\/\/www.mccannworldgroup.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">McCann Worldgroup<\/a> is the parent company of eight businesses, including the well-known, global advertising agency McCann Erickson &mdash; in turn well known for <a href=\"http:\/\/nymag.com\/daily\/entertainment\/2010\/08\/mccann_erikson_responds_to_mad.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">acquiring Sterling Cooper in 1963<\/a> &mdash; and brand agency Futurebrand. McCann Worldgroup is owned by giant Interpublic Group. At the beginning of the year McCann Worldgroup announced the launch of a new identity, designed by <a href=\"http:\/\/www.futurebrand.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Futurebrand<\/a>, and it has been gradually rolling out this year.<\/p><!--more--><blockquote>As our new tagline suggests, &#8216;transforming brands and growing businesses&#8217; is a promise that applies not only to our clients&#8217; businesses, but also to our own. We endeavor to pioneer the marketing solutions business by first succeeding in marketing our unique set of talents and our unrivaled global community. To that end, we are unveiling a new vibrant corporate identity created by FutureBrand as the banner under which we provide a unified offering in the marketplace.<br \/>&mdash; <a href=\"http:\/\/mccannworldtnt.blogspot.com\/2011\/01\/new-look-for-mccann-erickson-worldgroup.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">McCann Erickson Trinidad Blog<\/a><\/blockquote>\n<br \/>\n<object width=\"574\" height=\"298\" data=\"https:\/\/myworldgroup.com\/wgn\/wp-content\/plugins\/VydioPlayer\/vp_assets\/player.swf\" type=\"application\/x-shockwave-flash\" bgcolor=\"#000000\" ><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\"postID=7249&amp;services=https:\/\/myworldgroup.com\/wgn\/2011\/01\/11\/message-from-nick-brien-3\/&amp;autostart=false\" \/><param name=\"src\" value=\"https:\/\/myworldgroup.com\/wgn\/wp-content\/plugins\/VydioPlayer\/vp_assets\/player.swf\" \/><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" \/><param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\" \/><embed src=\"https:\/\/myworldgroup.com\/wgn\/wp-content\/plugins\/VydioPlayer\/vp_assets\/player.swf\" type=\"application\/x-shockwave-flash\" bgcolor=\"#000000\" flashvars=\"postID=7249&amp;services=https:\/\/myworldgroup.com\/wgn\/2011\/01\/11\/message-from-nick-brien-3\/&amp;autostart=false\" wmode=\"transparent\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"574\" height=\"298\"><\/embed><\/object>\n<br \/>\n<p class=\"caption\">Brand video. You can also see this on McCann&#8217;s <a href=\"http:\/\/www.mccannworldgroup.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">home page<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mccann_wg_logos_white.png\" alt=\"McCann Worldgroup\" \/><p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mccann_wg_logos_black.png\" alt=\"McCann Worldgroup\" \/><p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mccan_wg_reception.jpg\" alt=\"McCann Worldgroup\" \/><p>\n<p class=\"caption\">A few more application images, like the one above, at McCann&#8217;s <a href=\"http:\/\/www.facebook.com\/media\/set\/?set=a.109511379134819.19417.109463035806320\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Facebook page<\/a> &mdash; some of the images are strangely diminutive.<\/p>\n<p>Anything that rids the world of logos with lame dots gets my compliments. To different extents, of course. This new flexible identity for McCann is decent in concept &mdash; using the &#8220;M&#8221; and &#8220;W&#8221;, which are visually opposites, to show other opposites like water and fire, spring and fall, bees and flowers, etc. &mdash; but the execution is very amateurish. Other than the fire and water iteration, all versions look like first rounds of Illustrator and Photoshop work and there is no real consistency <em>or<\/em> enough inconsistency to make the whole better than the parts. Perhaps hiring a single illustrator that could bring all these concepts to life would have been a more interesting approach. It also feels a bit too playful and naive for such a serious network of agencies. But, again, no more dots&hellip;.<\/p>\n<p class=\"bottom\">Thanks to <a href=\"http:\/\/www.diabrands.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Kenny<\/a> for the tip.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_110602_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_110602_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv1\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_110602_config_02.xml&#038;xyz=poll_110602_votes_02.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv2\");\n\t\t\/\/ ]]&gt;\n\t}\n\t-->\n<\/script>\n<!--START DATA TABLE-->\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/divider_voting_start.gi